bio.experienceSummary:
I am a hardworking by mom of two, an 17-year-old and a 13-year-old. I have plenty of experience with children of all ages. 

Im currently A Nanny to a 4 and 6year-old. I've been with this family since the oldest was 2 and the baby since birth. I have extensive childcare experience. 

Unfortunately I have to move on due to both children being in school full time. 

I'm a non smoker. Reliable and trustworthy and patient. 
I have my own transportation. English Speaking and Pet Friendly.

Hello! My name is Kellie. I am originally from long Island and relocated to Staten Island about 3 years ago. I have experience in babysitting and also have been a full time nanny at one point. I have references for all upon request. I think its important to provide children with a fun, fulfilling and enriched environment. I am an enthusiastic and responsible person and look forward to meeting you and your kids!

Hi! My name is Citlalli A :) I'm a positive and energetic college student. I am currently a teacher assistant at a daycare! I love working with kids. I'm looking for a way to earn a little extra money while doing the thing I love. I'm confident, energetic, and fun. I will be more than happy to meet you and your kiddo soon!

Hello! I am a 27-year-old middle school language arts teacher living in Woodbridge, NJ. I AM FULLY COVID-19 VACCINATED!! I have my bachelor's degree in English and my Master's in Teaching with certifications in k-6, special ed., and middle school (5-8) language arts. Personally, I have worked with children for as long as I can remember with jobs such as babysitting, assistant preschool teacher, arts & craft specialist at my local summer camp, and my recent teaching experience. I have experience with children ages newborn through 8th grade as well as children with special needs. I can also provide you with references if needed!

**I am a full time teacher during the year and am not looking for reoccurring weekday jobs**

description.displayText: Melissa was our summer babysitter for our two boys (elementary school age) for two summers (2019 and 2020).  Melissa truly loves children; she took the boys to the library, the park, to get ice cream after camp.  Melissa became part of our family and she will always be. My boys adore her.  We wish that she lived closer so she can babysit for us again this summer.

bio.experienceSummary: I have two beautiful children ages 23 and 14. My 14-year-old has autism severity of , nonverbal and extremely behavioral! Inresult I had to stop working ti become his advocate to give him the services he was was lacking! Now that I finally have him in a stable school, provides me with the freedom to go back to work withing his school hours! I am hard worker, trustworthy and will be committed!

Positive, calm, balanced, committed, ambitious, compassionate, reliable, kind and very creative. My 2 daughters are my highest achievement making me proud every single day. In the past I worked as a Art teacher for kids with disabilities at "Special School Sacel" Romania. Between 2000 and 2005 I was part of an amazing French nonprofit organization "L'École de clown" where I was doing art therapy with homeless kids. I am in the process of getting a degree in Art Therapy so I could use my creative skills to help kids and adults to express themselves through art. I am very patient, caring and nurturing person, highly skilled in educational activities to stimulate physical, social and cognitive development of the child. I have also worked for many years as a baby sitter and floating lead teacher in daycare setting. Babysit children between 1 month to 10 years old. Recently I received my certification for CPR, First Aid and AED.

description.displayText:
I am writing to express my recommendation for Camelia M. Cami has worked as a babysitter for my two year old toddler for the last 9 months. She serves as an excellent role model to my young child. My daughter always looked forward to her time with Cami and are always very sad to see her leave. She used to do lot of great art work and read her books and teach her lessons of life. 
She is a very kind and responsible person. She has never given me reason to believe that she could not handle any situation that was put before her. You would be very fortunate to hire her as an employee

bio.experienceSummary: I grew up in a big family both immediate and extended. I am the oldest of seven and I have been surrounded by babies/young children my entire life. I also babysit at school. I have been with that family for almost two years now and continue to have a good relationship with them. I am trustworthy, responsible, and reliable.

description.displayText: Kayleigh has been our babysitter for the past 4 years.  My kids love it when she watches them because she is fun, plays games with them and has even taken them out to dinner. We have had such a great experience with Kayleigh. She is reliable and responsible and a great role model. We are lucky to have her and your family would be too.

bio.experienceSummary:
I love kids and kids love me! I have a lot of experience babysitting and nannying for families with children of all ages. I have had experience working at a daycare center in the preschool and infant rooms. I have also worked as a camp counselor for over 5 years at various performing arts camps and programs, and interned as an English TA at a high school in Vienna, Austria. The children I work with love me because am just as fun and imaginative as they are. Here is a poem one of my 12 yr old Austrian students wrote for me: Singer, Active, Much Fun, Always happy, Natural, Theater, Honest.

I am looking for a part time nanny position with consistent hours that work with my grad school schedule.

Starting in May or June (possibly sooner), I will be available to work full days Wednesday-Friday.

description.originalText: Sam has been caring for our daughter since she was 7 months old (she is now 2!) and has been so wonderful. She is gentle, sweet, caring, and attentive. She drives my daughter weekly to classes and is always careful and cautious. She handles meltdowns and tantrums with calmness and ease, which is especially helpful for the big feelings our 2 year old has. She has been such a help to our family.

bio.experienceSummary: Hi My name is Darleen and I am Dedicated, Caring, Honest, Reliable mother of two grown daughters ages 18 & 30. I have worked for the city for 20 years and have been retired for four years now. I have experience with children of all ages from infant and up. I am available Monday-Friday 6am-6pm

Hello, 
My name is Shalayne. I am a 38-year-old woman who has been around kids for all of my life. Growing up with 4 younger siblings, I was pretty much my mother's helper with everything. I have been in the child care business for the better side of 20 years working with ages from infant to 20 years old. I was also a preschool teacher for 2years and a ABA para professional for 4 years in NJ. I would love to meet with you to see if we are a great fit for each other. Thank you for taking the time out and reading my application. Hope to hear from you soon and have an amazing day.

description.originalText: Shalayne is a dedicated and a giving person with children. She goes above and beyond. She also has great communication with parents, which is very important when it comes to this kind of work. I highly recommend Shalayne. To top it off, she has tons of experience and is aware of children’s cognitive abilities and development.
